text.tspan: Pyramid Web Server + sockjs server: http://localhost:8001/__pyramid_router__
Roles (*) are partner's roles, offered as own roles, that are explicitly configured and hired.
Extra-roles (^) are dynamic roles, set by a client connecion. When the client gaplic is down, they reconnect and the roles are recovered.
They serve to know the back way.
Extra-roles (^^) are dynamic roles, set when a event go cross intermediate gaplics. They are necessary to know the back way.
If a gaplic is down he lose their ^extra-roles, and until a new event arrives, he don't know back ways.
One solution is broadcast to the static routes, a registration update every time that a dynamic connection is up.
Better with configuration: broadcast dynamic roles: bool (the bank don't have to broadcast dynamic role of currantes: too much!!
If a known dynamic role arrives, they are ignored and no go cross forward. Avoid infinite circular loop.
Por registrarse, se suscribe a un sorteo.
Al establecer la ruta estática en el envio de la identity_card van también los
roles de back-way, que son todos los roles de las conexiones dinámicas.
Cuando uno recibe una identity_card de una conexión dinámica,
si obtiene nuevos roles, debe reenviar su identity card (back ways modificados)
Si el nuevo rol recibido es el propio, se abstendrá de reenviar,
